Integration test suite (ported from `test/snippet.test.ts`) validating LSP snippet-body rendering and the two nvim-facing artifacts (`plover_keys` and `snippets` maps) produced by `steno::build_snippets`. Runs against the real `dict.steno` corpus at the repo root, loaded via `corpus()`/`typed()` helpers, plus one hand-built `TypedEntry` (`template_literal()`) for the `` `${%0}` `` template case whose original corpus stroke `STKWR-LT` was repurposed (now means a `let` binding) — this file constructs that `TypedEntry` directly rather than looking it up, so it will silently keep testing stale behavior if `render_snippet`'s handling of single-tabstop templates changes without a corresponding corpus stroke to cross-check against.

Key coupling: asserts on exact strings from `dict.steno` (e.g. stroke `STKWR-PBGS/TPH-FLT` must render to `"function ${1}(${2}): number {\n${0}\\}"`), so edits to that corpus entry or to `render_snippet`'s escaping/tabstop logic break these tests directly. Also asserts the Plover-token wire format: `{^}<SENTINEL_OPEN><stroke><SENTINEL_CLOSE>{^}` for terminals, and plain `{^}<text>{^}` (no sentinel) for non-terminal partials — any change to `SENTINEL_OPEN`/`SENTINEL_CLOSE` or the wrapping convention in the main crate must be mirrored in `plover_token_wrapped`, `non_terminal_plover_key_has_no_sentinel`, and `family_root_plover_key_has_no_sentinel`.

Notable invariants under test: a stroke that is a strict `/`-prefix of another stroke must never be `terminal` (`no_terminal_is_a_prefix_of_another_stroke` is a corpus-wide safety net against a buffer-corruption class of bug involving "family-root" strokes like `STKWR-PBGS`, `STKWR*PLT`, `STKWR-RBGT`); `build_snippets` must produce zero key collisions; the corpus must yield 1000+ snippet bodies and every terminal's Plover token must resolve to one. `tabstop_count` counts `${0}`..`${9}` occurrences only (no multi-digit tabstop support assumed). Helpers `corpus()`, `typed()`, `by_stroke()` are local to this file and read from `CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR/../../dict.steno` — moving the crate or the dict file breaks every test here.